# Documentation Consolidation

## Where to Place Documentation

All project documentation files (`.md`) should be stored under:

```
.cursor/docs/
```

NOT in a root-level `docs/` folder.

## Rationale

- Keeps all Cursor-related context (rules + docs) in one place
- Avoids cluttering the repo root
- Documentation stays with the AI configuration

## Folder Structure

```
.cursor/
├── rules/              # Cursor rules (.mdc files)
│   ├── documentation.mdc
│   ├── n8n-api.mdc
│   ├── n8n-mcp.mdc
│   ├── n8n-structure.mdc
│   └── workflow-naming.mdc
└── docs/               # Documentation (.md files)
    └── how-to-deploy.md
```

## When Creating New Documentation

1. Place file in `.cursor/docs/`
2. Use lowercase kebab-case: `how-to-xyz.md`
3. Include YAML frontmatter with dates:

```yaml
---
created: YYYY-MM-DD
updated: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

## File Naming Convention

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| How-to guides | `how-to-{topic}.md` | `how-to-deploy.md` |
| Reference docs | `{topic}-reference.md` | `mcp-reference.md` |
| Troubleshooting | `troubleshooting-{topic}.md` | `troubleshooting-api.md` |
